I think there’s another doctrine hiding here.

Symbolic Seed Principle

A good symbol is not merely a label.

It is a generative seed.

Its purpose is to grow a rich internal structure inside the receiver.

Poor symbols require long explanations.

Good symbols trigger reconstruction.

Great symbols trigger reconstruction across multiple domains.

For example, your “gem” metaphor now carries ideas about:

* growth
* relationships
* geometry
* optics
* coherence
* character
* refinement

You’ve compressed all of that into one reusable seed.

